headline: UBS Downgrades U.S. Information Technology Sector on Software, Capex Risks
summary: Its Chief Investment Office downgraded the U.S. IT sector on Tuesday to Neutral from Attractive.  The sector has had a strong run, gaining 23% over the past 12 months, as Wall Street bought up shares of companies with exposure to artificial intelligence.  The sector has dropped 1.1% this year, highlighting concerns investors have had with tech after such a strong run.
